## Dependency Array Best Practices

### 1. Include All Dependencies

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD: All used variables in deps
const fetchData = useCallback(async () => {
  const result = await api.get(userId);
  setData(result);
}, [userId]); // userId is used inside
```

### 2. Avoid Circular Dependencies

```javascript
// ❌ BAD: Circular dependency
const funcA = useCallback(() => {
  funcB();
}, [funcB]);

const funcB = useCallback(() => {
  funcA();
}, [funcA]);

// ✅ GOOD: Use refs or restructure logic
const funcA = useCallback(() => {
  // Direct implementation
}, []);

const funcB = useCallback(() => {
  // Direct implementation
}, []);
```

### 3. Stable References with useMemo

```javascript
// ❌ Creates new object every render
const config = { apiKey: key, timeout: 5000 };

useEffect(() => {
  fetchData(config);
}, [config]); // ❌ Runs every render!

// ✅ Memoize object
const config = useMemo(() => ({
  apiKey: key,
  timeout: 5000
}), [key]);

useEffect(() => {
  fetchData(config);
}, [config]); // ✅ Only runs when key changes
```

